The paper discusses the Prolog debugger and its compatibility with declarative programming, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). It also touches upon logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) concepts, as Prolog is often used in these fields. Additionally, the paper discusses the adequacy of the Prolog debugger, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) topic.
